s unorthodox in the matter of rituals. A=\r\nbove all, he fearlessly follows his convictions and does not engage in ritu=\r\nals that he does not consider meaningful. He is also against following the =\r\nletter of the rules and breaking the spirit. For example, when he went to a=\r\n griha pravesh (housewarming) ceremony once, they were beating a cow to for=\r\nce it to climb stairs to enter the room. People bring a cow into the room a=\r\nt the time of housewarming, as they consider a cow to symbolize Lakshmi and=\r\n some steps in the ritual require a cow\n in the room. As the cow was not ha=\r\nppy to climb stairs, they resorted to violence to force it. My father was s=\r\nad to see the suffering of the cow and told them bluntly that they were doi=\r\nng adharma and there was no point in getting a cow in the room like that. B=\r\nut my father puts more value on the spirit of the rules rather than the let=\r\nter and does not hesitate to speak his mind in front of anybody.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For=\r\n my upanayanam, he took me to Lord Venkateswara temple in Tirupati/Tirumala=\r\n, which is his favorite temple. At the time of muhurta, we were on the hill=\r\n near the temple. He spent a few hours doing his japam with various stotras=\r\n and I also did japam with several stotras. When the muhurta came, he simpl=\r\ny taught me Gayatri mantra and that was it. No rituals of any kind were per=\r\nformed, except for japam for a few hours.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In my opinion, such a simp=\r\nle approach is also perfectly fine. The key points are that the person givi=\r\nng mantra should have done some\n sadhana, both of them should be in a good =\r\nand relaxed mood at the time and environment should be peaceful, and, the p=\r\nerson receiving mantra should do a lot of sadhana with it later on.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\nIf a businessman opens an account in his son&#39;s name for a new business vent=\r\nure by the young man, what matters is how much money father gave and how we=\r\nll the son used the money, how he ran the new business and how he grew the =\r\nmoney. How big a party was held, how many people came and what activities t=\r\nhey engaged in is irrelevant in the long run.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;My purpos=\r\ne is not to discourage elaborate rituals. Do them if there is social pressu=\r\nre to do so or you find them interesting. But, atleast ensure that mantropa=\r\ndesa happens peacefully and correctly. More importantly, ensure that the yo=\r\nung man does some sadhana with Gayatri mantra everyday, after upanayanam.&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Also, it is perfectly acceptable (and beneficial) to initiate the you=\r\nng person into homam\n after upanayanam is done. On the same day or a few da=\r\nys later, one can teach a simple version of Ganapathi homam and let the you=\r\nng person perform it by oneself during weekends or so. One can start off wi=\r\nth the super-short procedure and slowly add things. Doing Gayatri mantra ev=\r\neryday and homam now and then will accelerate the spiritual evolution of th=\r\ne young person.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;----------------------=\r\n------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish=\r\n Lessons, Jyotish Writings,&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Ho=\r\nmam and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; targe=\r\nt=3D_blank rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Films that =\r\nmake a difference: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://saraswatifilms.org/&quot; target=3D_blank r=\r\nel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Spirituality: &lt;A href=3D&quot;htt=\r\np://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&quot; target=3D_blank\n rel=3Dnofollow&gt;ht=\r\ntp://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Jyotish writings: &lt;A href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&quo